 This can go on until some condition has been met, for instance until the
 change between two subsequent estimates of 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho$
\end_inset

 is smaller than some small number (i.e.
 a convergence tolerance level) or until a maximum number of iterations
 has been surpassed.
\end_layout

